<TITLE> Home secretaries meet in Delhi Aug 2-3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 31 (bdnews24.com) - A 12-member Bangladesh delegation leaves for New Delhi Wednesday to attend the eighth home secretary-level meeting in the Indian capital on August 2-3. The government said in a statement that the delegation, led by home secretary Abdul Karim, would also include the director general of Bangladesh Rifles, a joint secretary of the home ministry, additional inspector general of police, a director general of the foreign ministry and representatives of the Joint Rivers Commission (JRC). In addition, the Bangladesh high commissioner to India and other officials of the High Commission would also be present at the meeting. The meeting is likely to discuss disputatious border issues as well as other related matters of mutual interest. The Bangladesh delegation is expected to return August 6. bd
